Matt NAQUIN v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7681. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 28, 1937. Alfred A. May,. of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. John C. Lehr, of Detroit, Mich., for appellee.

Before HICKS and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

HICKS, Circuit Judge.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel, it is ordered that this appeal be and the same is dismissed, without costs to either party.
